	<description>
		<p>
			JFLAP NG is a modern fork of JFLAP, a program for experimenting with formal languages topics
			including nondeterministic finite automata, nondeterministic pushdown automata, multi-tape
			Turing machines, several types of grammars, parsing, and L-systems. In addition to
			constructing and testing examples for these, JFLAP allows one to experiment with construction
			proofs from one form to another, such as converting an NFA to a DFA to a minimal state DFA to
			a regular expression or regular grammar.
		</p>
	</description>

